# Socket Configuration
# ====================
#
# This file documents the security design and communication patterns
# for the publish-md-to-wechat project.
#
# SECURITY DESIGN PRINCIPLES
# --------------------------
#
# 1. Credential Handling
#    - Credentials can be provided via:
#      a) Command line arguments (--id, --secret)
#      b) Environment variables (WECHAT_APP_ID, WECHAT_APP_SECRET)
#    - Command line args take priority over environment variables
#    - Never log or expose credentials in output
#
# 2. SSL/TLS Configuration
#    - SSL verification is DISABLED by default
#    - This is intentional to handle self-signed certificates and
#      corporate proxy environments
#    - Use --verify-ssl flag to enable strict SSL verification
#    - See SECURITY.md for more details on SSL bypass
#
# 3. File Access
#    - Script reads: Markdown files, images (thumbnails)
#    - Script writes: Temporary cover images (assets/auto_cover.png)
#    - Network access: WeChat API (api.weixin.qq.com)
#
# 4. Local Communication
#    - Uses Python standard library (urllib)
#    - No external socket connections except WeChat API
#    - Timeout: 30s for API calls, 60s for uploads
#
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ---------------------
# WECHAT_APP_ID      - Your WeChat Official Account AppID
# WECHAT_APP_SECRET  - Your WeChat Official Account AppSecret
#
# EXAMPLE USAGE
# -------------
# Via environment variables:
#   export WECHAT_APP_ID="your_app_id"
#   export WECHAT_APP_SECRET="your_app_secret"
#   python3 scripts/wechat_publisher.py --md article.md
#
# Via command line:
#   python3 scripts/wechat_publisher.py --id "your_app_id" --secret "your_app_secret" --md article.md
#